You haven't thought about your old butler.

269
00:29:21,910 --> 00:29:22,170
Bang!

270
00:29:26,380 --> 00:29:30,320
People from your world have so much to lose.

271
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:35,320
Now you think, because your mommy and your daddy got shot,

272
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:38,560
you know about the ugly side of life, but you don't.

273
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:40,480
You've never tasted desperate.

274
00:29:41,260 --> 00:29:44,000
You're Bruce Wayne, the Prince of Gotham.

275
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,700
You'd have to go a thousand miles to meet someone who didn't know your name.

276
00:29:46,820 --> 00:29:51,640
So don't come down here with your anger, trying to prove something to yourself.

277
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:55,260
This is a world you never understand, and you always fear.

278
00:29:56,530 --> 00:29:57,470
what you don't understand.

279
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,160
Yeah, you got spirit, kid.

280
00:30:12,160 --> 00:30:12,920
I'll give you that.

281
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,180
More than your old man, anyway.

282
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,580
In the joint, Chill told me, uh,

283
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:19,860
told me about the night he killed your parents.

284
00:30:20,580 --> 00:30:22,200
He said your father begged for mercy.

285
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:26,600
Like a dog.

286
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:41,420
Should've did better.

287
00:30:52,130 --> 00:30:52,750
For what?

288
00:30:53,010 --> 00:30:53,470
Your jacket.

289
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:54,920
Okay.

290
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:57,790
Hey, hey, hey.

291
00:30:58,350 --> 00:31:00,250
Let me have some nice coat.

292
00:31:00,550 --> 00:31:02,030
He carefully sees you with that.

293
00:31:03,390 --> 00:31:04,570
They're gonna come looking for me.

294
00:31:04,750 --> 00:31:04,970
Who?

295
00:31:05,810 --> 00:31:35,440
Everyone, among the criminals, did you start to pity them?

296
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:45,080
The first time I stole so that I wouldn't starve, yes, I lost many assumptions about the simple nature of right and wrong.

297
00:31:47,220 --> 00:31:54,980
And when I traveled, I learned the fear before a crime and the thrill of success.

298
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,960
But I never became one of them.

299
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:05,260
Fool. What the hell do I care what your name is? You're a criminal.

300
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:06,340
What was your friend, Yuen?

301
00:32:06,620 --> 00:32:08,140
Tell that to the guy who owned these.

302
00:32:12,100 --> 00:32:15,750
You've traveled the world to understand the criminal mind, conquer your fears.

303
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:20,740
The criminal is not complicated.

304
00:32:22,470 --> 00:32:24,510
What you really fear is inside yourself.

305
00:32:26,020 --> 00:32:27,680
You fear your own power.

306
00:32:28,760 --> 00:32:29,680
You fear your anger.

307
00:32:30,420 --> 00:32:34,080
The drive to do great or terrible things.

308
00:32:34,900 --> 00:32:45,450
Now, when he inwards, breathe.

309
00:33:10,100 --> 00:33:11,960
To conquer fear, you must become fear.

310
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,880
You must bask in the fear of other men.

311
00:33:17,870 --> 00:33:19,970
And men fear most what they cannot see.

312
00:33:38,380 --> 00:33:40,200
You have to become a terrible thought.

313
00:33:40,860 --> 00:33:53,890
You have to become an idea!

314
00:33:54,230 --> 00:36:06,870
You have to lead these men.

315
00:36:13,670 --> 00:36:16,430
But first, you must demonstrate your commitment to...

316
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:18,120
I avoid!

317
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:49,760
...but to fight criminals, this man is a murderer.

318
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:50,390
He's married.

319
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:53,230
By whom? Corrupt bureaucrats?

320
00:36:54,150 --> 00:36:56,070
Criminals mock society's laws.

321
00:36:56,770 --> 00:36:58,030
You know there's better than most.

322
00:37:03,470 --> 00:37:06,450
are prepared to do what is necessary to defeat evil.

323
00:37:06,870 --> 00:37:09,140
Or would I be leading these men?

324
00:37:15,310 --> 00:37:17,590
To strike at the heart of criminality.

325
00:37:19,670 --> 00:37:21,610
Gotham's time has come.

326
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:25,160
Like Constantinople or Rome before it.

327
00:37:26,140 --> 00:37:29,300
The city has become a breeding ground for suffering and injustice.

328
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:33,440
It is beyond saving and must be allowed to die.

329
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:37,970
This is the most important function of the league.

330
00:37:39,700 --> 00:37:41,540
It is one we performed for centuries.

331
00:41:04,490 --> 00:41:07,070
I will tell him you said he's alive.

332
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:28,700
Master Wayne, you've been gone a long time.

333
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:29,640
Yes, I have.

334
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:30,860
You look very fashionable.

335
00:41:32,830 --> 00:41:33,530
Apart from the mud.

336
00:41:34,570 --> 00:41:36,290
Were you coming back to Gotham for long, sir?

337
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:38,180
As long as it takes.

338
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:42,020
I'm going to show the people of Gotham their city doesn't belong to the criminals.

339
00:41:44,090 --> 00:41:48,470
In the Depression, your father nearly bankrupted Wayne Enterprises combating poverty.

340
00:41:48,870 --> 00:41:53,330
He believed that his example could inspire the wealthy of Gotham to save their city.

341
00:41:53,810 --> 00:41:54,090
Did it?

342
00:41:56,450 --> 00:42:00,640
In a way, their murder shocked the wealthy and the powerful into action.

343
00:42:03,170 --> 00:42:06,350
People need dramatic examples to shake them out of apathy,

344
00:42:06,370 --> 00:42:07,730
and I can't do that as Bruce Wayne.

345
00:42:08,220 --> 00:42:10,680
As a man, I'm flesh and blood.

346
00:42:10,680 --> 00:42:13,080
I can be ignored, I can be destroyed, but as a symbol,

347
00:42:15,970 --> 00:42:19,390
as a symbol, I can be everlasting.

348
00:42:20,490 --> 00:42:20,950
What symbol?

349
00:42:21,890 --> 00:42:22,270
Something.

350
00:42:26,520 --> 00:42:28,560
I assume that as you're taking on the underworld,

351
00:42:28,700 --> 00:42:33,540
this symbol is a persona to protect those you care about from reprisals.

352
00:42:34,140 --> 00:42:35,040
You thinking about Rachel?

353
00:42:35,620 --> 00:42:37,540
Hey, Rita, I was thinking of myself.

354
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:41,550
You told anyone I'm coming back?

355
00:42:42,010 --> 00:42:42,930
I just couldn't figure.

356
00:42:43,430 --> 00:42:45,990
The legal ramifications are bringing you back from the dead.

357
00:42:46,410 --> 00:42:46,590
Dead?

358
00:42:47,190 --> 00:42:48,230
You've been gone seven years.

359
00:42:48,470 --> 00:42:49,630
You had me declared dead?

360
00:42:49,890 --> 00:42:52,590
Well, actually, it was Mr. Earl. He's taking the company public.

361
00:42:52,950 --> 00:42:55,170
He wanted to liquidate your majority shareholding.

362
00:42:55,230 --> 00:42:56,690
Those shares are worth quite a bit of money.

363
00:42:57,960 --> 00:43:00,120
Well, it's a good thing I left everything to you, then.

364
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:01,880
Quite so, sir.

365
00:43:03,090 --> 00:43:04,550
And you can borrow the rolls, if you like.

366
00:43:04,830 --> 00:43:06,090
Just bring it back with a full tank.

367
00:43:06,650 --> 00:43:21,270
In my opinion, Mr. Zaz is as much a danger to himself as to others.

368
00:43:21,870 --> 00:43:25,270
And prison is probably not the best environment for his rehabilitation.

369
00:43:28,750 --> 00:43:29,290
Dr. Crane?

370
00:43:30,190 --> 00:43:30,990
Oh, Mr. Oz.

371
00:43:31,510 --> 00:43:34,510
You really think a man who butchers people for the mob doesn't belong in jail?

372
00:43:34,910 --> 00:43:37,370
Well, I would hardly have testified to that otherwise when I missed Oz.

373
00:43:37,730 --> 00:43:42,250
This is the third of Carmine Falcone's thugs you had declared insane and moved into your asylum.

374
00:43:42,650 --> 00:43:46,070
Well, the work offered by organized crime must have an attraction to the insane.

375
00:43:48,810 --> 00:43:49,610
Or the corrupt.

376
00:43:53,070 --> 00:43:56,830
Mr. Finch, I think you should check with Miss Dawes here

377
00:43:56,890 --> 00:43:59,450
just what implications your office has authorized her to make.

378
00:44:00,310 --> 00:44:00,670
If any.

379
00:44:05,300 --> 00:44:06,020
What are you doing, Rachel?

380
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:07,220
What are you doing, Carl?

381
00:44:07,820 --> 00:44:08,640
Looking out for you.

382
00:44:11,710 --> 00:44:13,110
Falcone is half the city.

383
00:44:13,590 --> 00:44:14,410
Bought and paid for.

384
00:44:15,570 --> 00:44:16,650
How can you say that?

385
00:44:16,990 --> 00:44:18,710
Because as much as I care about getting Falcone,

386
00:44:18,850 --> 00:44:19,910
I care more about you.

387
00:44:20,710 --> 00:44:21,190
That's sweet.

388
00:44:56,130 --> 00:44:56,710
Bless you, Pat.

389
00:44:56,710 --> 00:44:57,230
They get some.

390
00:44:57,870 --> 00:44:59,170
They nest somewhere in the grounds.

391
00:44:59,890 --> 00:47:05,550
Don't you mind, Doc? I'm bringing in the shipments.

392
00:47:06,270 --> 00:47:07,330
We are paying you for that.

393
00:47:07,750 --> 00:47:10,190
Maybe money isn't as interesting to me as Favis.

394
00:47:12,620 --> 00:47:16,900
I am more than aware that you are not intimidated by me, Mr. Falco.

395
00:47:17,680 --> 00:47:19,360
But you know who I'm working for.

396
00:47:19,860 --> 00:47:21,120
And when he gets here...

397
00:47:21,700 --> 00:47:22,640
He's coming to Gotham?

398
00:47:23,100 --> 00:47:23,660
Yes, he is.

399
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:28,600
And when he gets here, he's not going to want to hear that you have endangered our operation

400
00:47:28,720 --> 00:47:30,920
just to get your thugs out of a little jail time.

401
00:47:33,270 --> 00:47:34,170
Who's bothering you?

402
00:47:34,590 --> 00:47:36,190
There's a girl at the DA's office.

403
00:47:37,210 --> 00:47:38,810
We'll buy a Roth, not this one.

404
00:47:40,170 --> 00:47:41,030
Idealist, huh?

405
00:47:42,210 --> 00:47:43,650
Well, there's an answer to that, too.

406
00:47:51,430 --> 00:47:54,410
No, we are showing very healthy growth in these sectors.

407
00:47:55,090 --> 00:48:00,210
I don't think that Thomas Wayne would have viewed heavy arms manufacture as a suitable cornerstone for our business.

408
00:48:00,910 --> 00:48:03,150
It's 20 years ago.

409
00:48:06,110 --> 00:48:11,610
I think after 20 years we can allow ourselves to stop thinking about what Thomas Wayne would have done.

410
00:48:12,310 --> 00:48:13,570
Good morning, Mr. Earl's office.

411
00:48:14,410 --> 00:48:16,170
Oh, yes, he's confirmed for the dinner tomorrow evening.

412
00:48:17,850 --> 00:48:18,290
Good morning.

413
00:48:19,290 --> 00:48:20,690
I'm here to see you, Mr. Earl.

414
00:48:21,450 --> 00:48:21,690
Name?

415
00:48:23,030 --> 00:48:23,830
Bruce Wayne.

416
00:48:26,890 --> 00:48:29,850
Thomas would probably not have taken the company public,

417
00:48:30,270 --> 00:48:34,150
but that is what we as responsible managers are going to do.

418
00:48:35,380 --> 00:48:35,680
Jessica.

419
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:39,420
Jessica, where are you?

420
00:48:42,450 --> 00:48:43,490
I want to answer your phone.

421
00:48:45,610 --> 00:48:48,850
It's Wayne Enterprises, Mr. Earl. I'm sure they'll call back.

422
00:48:49,130 --> 00:48:51,350
Bruce, you're supposed to be dead.

423
00:48:51,950 --> 00:48:52,670
Sorry to disappoint.

424
00:48:53,750 --> 00:48:54,990
I need you to take a look at this.

425
00:48:55,330 --> 00:48:56,610
Have you seen him yet?

426
00:48:56,970 --> 00:48:57,150
Who?

427
00:48:57,950 --> 00:48:58,190
Wayne.

428
00:48:58,770 --> 00:48:59,510
He's been over the news.

429
00:49:00,190 --> 00:49:00,630
He's back.

430
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:06,800
I'm sure you realize I can't stop.

431
00:49:06,900 --> 00:49:08,940
Big machine, too many wheels turning.

432
00:49:09,020 --> 00:49:09,760
We're going public.

433
00:49:10,240 --> 00:49:10,740
I understand.

434
00:49:11,780 --> 00:49:14,080
And I'll be handsomely rewarded for my shares.

435
00:49:14,780 --> 00:49:16,100
I'm not looking to interfere.

436
00:49:17,580 --> 00:49:18,920
I am looking for a job.

437
00:49:19,460 --> 00:49:19,620
Oh?

438
00:49:19,940 --> 00:49:22,580
I just want to get to know the company that my family built.

439
00:49:23,420 --> 00:49:24,880
Any ideas where you would start?

440
00:49:25,700 --> 00:49:27,780
Applied Sciences caught my eye.

441
00:49:28,460 --> 00:49:29,160
Fox Department.

442
00:49:30,350 --> 00:49:31,190
I let him know you're coming.

443
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:34,020
You look like him.

444
00:49:34,660 --> 00:49:35,700
Yeah, your dad.

445
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:38,860
You're the only one left of the Wayne family.

446
00:49:39,580 --> 00:49:40,780
This is where you belong.

447
00:49:42,530 --> 00:49:43,190
Welcome home.

448
00:49:43,730 --> 00:49:46,310
Environmental procedures, defense projects,

449
00:49:46,470 --> 00:49:47,270
consumer products,

450
00:49:48,940 --> 00:49:49,620
all prototypes.

451
00:49:50,600 --> 00:49:51,320
Not in production.

452
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:52,700
On any level whatsoever.

453
00:49:53,660 --> 00:49:53,940
None.

454
00:49:55,380 --> 00:49:56,900
What did they tell you this place was?

455
00:49:57,460 --> 00:49:58,400
They didn't tell me anything.

456
00:50:01,980 --> 00:50:03,500
Earl told me exactly what it was

457
00:50:03,700 --> 00:50:04,560
and sent me down here.

458
00:50:05,950 --> 00:50:06,510
Dead end.

459
00:50:07,550 --> 00:50:09,730
Place to keep me from causing the board any more trouble.

460
00:50:10,370 --> 00:50:14,200
You were on the board?

461
00:50:14,720 --> 00:50:15,820
When your father ran things.

462
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:16,740
You knew my father?

463
00:50:17,120 --> 00:50:19,280
Oh yeah, helped him build his train.

464
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:20,940
Oh, here we are.

465
00:50:25,680 --> 00:50:27,040
Kevlar utility harness,

466
00:50:27,700 --> 00:50:29,580
gas powered magnetic grapple gun,

467
00:50:29,860 --> 00:50:32,000
the 350 pound test monofilament.

468
00:50:35,410 --> 00:50:36,970
Wonderful project, your dad's train.

469
00:50:38,050 --> 00:50:39,730
Rided it right into Wayne town,

470
00:50:40,090 --> 00:50:42,090
along with the water and power utilities.

471
00:50:43,070 --> 00:50:45,770
I gotta make Wayne Tower the unofficial senator of Gotham City.

472
00:50:46,250 --> 00:50:47,910
Of course, Earl had to go to the rot. Here we are.

473
00:50:50,710 --> 00:50:52,810
Nomex survival suit for advanced infantry.

474
00:50:53,270 --> 00:50:55,790
Kevlar bi-weave, reinforced joints.

475
00:50:56,290 --> 00:50:56,890
Terror-resistant.

476
00:50:57,110 --> 00:50:58,290
This sucker will stop a knife.

477
00:50:58,650 --> 00:50:59,310
Bulletproof.

478
00:50:59,590 --> 00:51:00,770
Anything but a straight shot.

479
00:51:01,270 --> 00:51:02,490
Why didn't they put it into production?

480
00:51:02,970 --> 00:51:05,970
Bean counters didn't think a soldier's life was worth 300 grand.

481
00:51:08,930 --> 00:51:10,970
So, what's your interest in it, Mr. Wayne?

482
00:51:11,890 --> 00:51:14,890
I wanna borrow it for, uh, Spelunky.

483
00:51:16,290 --> 00:51:16,770
Spreling.

484
00:51:17,710 --> 00:51:18,770
Yeah, you know cave diving?

485
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:22,840
You're expecting to run into much gunfire in these caves?

486
00:51:23,520 --> 00:51:29,160
Look, I'd rather Mr. Earl didn't know about me borrowing.

487
00:51:30,500 --> 00:51:34,570
Mr. Wayne, the way I see it, all this stuff is yours anyway.

488
00:51:38,220 --> 00:51:39,700
You good? Give it a try.

489
00:51:44,990 --> 00:51:50,400
Charming. At least you'll have company.

490
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:56,460
This must be the lowest foundation of the South East Wing.

491
00:52:09,350 --> 00:52:13,150
In the Civil War, your great-great-grandfather was involved in the Underground Railroad,

492
00:52:13,490 --> 00:52:16,390
secretly transporting three slaves to the North.

493
00:52:16,730 --> 00:52:20,130
And I suspect these cabins came in handy.

494
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:38,160
I can see everything arrived from down here, sir. Thank you very much.

495
00:52:59,180 --> 00:53:01,050
Part of this cow from Singapore...

496
00:53:01,250 --> 00:53:02,410
...by a dummy corporation.

497
00:53:02,970 --> 00:53:08,730
Indeed. And then quite separately, we place an order through a Chinese company for these.

498
00:53:10,490 --> 00:53:11,050
Put it together ourselves.

499
00:53:11,050 --> 00:53:11,870
Precisely.

500
00:53:13,710 --> 00:53:16,640
There'll have to be large orders to avoid suspicion.

501
00:53:16,640 --> 00:53:17,270
How large?

502
00:53:17,270 --> 00:53:17,450
Say, 10,000.

503
00:53:19,070 --> 00:53:20,630
Well, at least we'll have spares.

504
00:53:22,970 --> 00:53:23,310
Yes.

505
00:53:42,990 --> 00:53:43,970
Don't suppose you want a taste.

506
00:53:44,990 --> 00:53:47,810
Just keep offering, thinking maybe someday you'll get wise.

507
00:53:48,590 --> 00:53:50,010
There's nothing wise in what you do, Flash.

508
00:53:50,930 --> 00:53:51,990
Well, Jimbo, you don't take the taste.

509
00:53:52,950 --> 00:53:53,870
Makes us guys nervous.

510
00:53:54,470 --> 00:53:55,130
I'm not a rat.

511
00:53:59,030 --> 00:54:02,270
In a town that's been, who's there to write to anyway?

512
00:54:32,470 --> 00:54:33,250
Don't turn around.

513
00:54:39,970 --> 00:54:42,890
Carmine Falcone brings a shitloads of drugs every week.

514
00:54:43,570 --> 00:54:44,970
Nobody takes him down. Why?

515
00:54:46,790 --> 00:54:48,270
He's paid up with the right people.

516
00:54:49,150 --> 00:54:50,550
What will it take to bring him down?

517
00:54:52,660 --> 00:54:53,960
Leverage on Judge Faden.

518
00:54:55,810 --> 00:54:57,790
And a DA right enough to prosecute.

519
00:54:58,490 --> 00:54:59,890
Rachel Dawes.

520
00:55:00,830 --> 00:55:01,470
Who are you?

521
00:55:02,230 --> 00:55:03,310
Watch for my side.

522
00:55:06,370 --> 00:55:07,390
You're just one man.

523
00:55:07,930 --> 00:55:49,510
What the hell was that?

524
00:55:53,790 --> 00:55:54,410
Just some nut.

525
00:55:58,790 --> 00:56:00,790
What is it today? More spelonky?

526
00:56:01,130 --> 00:56:03,550
No. Today it's base jumping.

527
00:56:04,290 --> 00:56:04,810
Base jumping?

528
00:56:06,410 --> 00:56:07,430
Is that like parachuting?

529
00:56:07,690 --> 00:56:12,180
Kinda. Do you have any lightweight fabrics?

530
00:56:13,160 --> 00:56:15,460
You know, I think I have just a thing.

531
00:56:17,140 --> 00:56:18,320
It's called memory cloth.

532
00:56:18,740 --> 00:56:19,280
Notice anything?

533
00:56:22,860 --> 00:56:23,720
Regularly flexible.

534
00:56:25,380 --> 00:56:31,040
But put a current through it, molecules realign, it becomes rigid.

535
00:56:31,320 --> 00:56:32,620
What kind of shapes can you make?

536
00:56:32,820 --> 00:56:35,620
It can be tailored to fit in any structure based on a rigid skeleton.

537
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:37,080
Too expensive for the Army?

538
00:56:37,460 --> 00:56:41,740
I don't think they ever tried to market it to the billionaire's belonging base dumping crowd.

539
00:56:42,260 --> 00:56:43,120
Look, Mr. Fox.

540
00:56:43,320 --> 00:56:43,640
Yes, sir?

541
00:56:44,900 --> 00:56:46,160
If you're uncomfortable...

542
00:56:46,160 --> 00:56:51,500
Mr. Wayne, if you don't want to tell me exactly what you're doing when I'm asked, I don't have to lie.

543
00:56:53,450 --> 00:56:54,970
But don't think of me as an idiot.

544
00:57:01,460 --> 00:57:01,960
What's that?

545
00:57:05,290 --> 00:57:06,020
Want a tumbler?

546
00:57:06,480 --> 00:57:17,510
It was built as a bridging vehicle.

547
00:57:19,510 --> 00:57:23,730
During combat, two of these would jump over a river, throwing caves.

548
00:57:26,320 --> 00:57:30,240
And over here on the throttle, flip that open and throttle up.

549
00:57:30,340 --> 00:57:32,240
This will boost you into a rampless jump.

550
00:57:32,560 --> 00:57:32,980
No, no!

551
00:57:41,330 --> 00:57:42,290
Disengaged.

552
00:57:42,910 --> 00:57:47,710
We never could get the damn bridge to work, but this baby works just fine.

553
00:57:48,290 --> 00:57:48,570
No!

554
00:57:57,490 --> 00:57:58,250
So what do you think?

555
00:57:59,970 --> 00:58:01,010
Does it come in black?

556
00:58:02,610 --> 00:58:04,570
I need you at the docks Thursday.

557
00:58:05,290 --> 00:58:05,930
Problems?

558
00:58:06,270 --> 00:58:08,290
I don't want any trouble with the last shipment.

559
00:58:08,730 --> 00:58:08,910
Sure.

560
00:58:11,010 --> 00:58:13,810
We're on the street is you gotta beef with somebody in the DA's office.

561
00:58:14,830 --> 00:58:15,350
That's not right.

562
00:58:15,590 --> 00:58:19,990
And that there's a fat prize waiting for anybody willing to do anything about it.

563
00:58:20,310 --> 00:58:22,050
So what's your point, Mr. Flass?

564
00:58:22,810 --> 00:58:23,610
Have you seen the girl?

565
00:58:24,410 --> 00:58:26,050
It's a cute little assistant DA.

566
00:58:27,270 --> 00:58:30,350
I think it's a little bit too much heat to bring down, maybe.

567
00:58:31,190 --> 00:58:32,090
Even for this town.

568
00:58:32,310 --> 00:58:34,110
Never underestimate Gotham City.

569
00:58:34,550 --> 00:58:37,070
People get mugged coming home from work every day of the week.

570
00:58:37,730 --> 00:58:39,990
Sometimes, sometimes things just go bad.

571
00:58:44,070 --> 00:58:48,270
Sir, the problem with the graphite, sir, the next 10,000 will be up to specifications.

572
00:58:48,670 --> 00:58:49,810
At least they gave us a discount.

573
00:58:50,820 --> 00:58:51,080
Quite.

574
00:58:51,820 --> 00:58:55,260
In the meantime, sir, may I suggest you try to avoid landing?

575
00:58:55,780 --> 00:58:56,260
On your head.

576
00:59:34,450 --> 00:59:35,910
White bats lost away.

577
00:59:36,630 --> 00:59:37,610
That's frightened me.

578
00:59:39,110 --> 00:59:40,670
This time my enemies shared my dread.

579
01:00:08,170 --> 01:00:08,630
What is this?

580
01:00:13,570 --> 01:00:13,930
Continue.

581
01:00:20,750 --> 01:00:21,730
Looks fine out there.

582
01:00:22,940 --> 01:00:24,540
Bears, they go straight to the dealers.

583
01:00:24,920 --> 01:00:27,500
Yeah, and the rabbits go to the man in the narrows.

584
01:00:27,680 --> 01:00:28,360
What's the difference?

585
01:00:28,820 --> 01:00:30,300
Ignorance is bliss, my friend.

586
01:00:30,960 --> 01:00:34,000
Don't burden yourself with these secrets of scary people.

587
01:00:50,130 --> 01:00:52,380
Hey, it's Dice.

588
01:00:52,380 --> 01:05:05,530
I wouldn't be too sure of that.

589
01:05:57,710 --> 01:06:00,940
Gangs, guardian angels, or the goddamn Salvation Army.

590
01:06:01,420 --> 01:06:03,440
Get them off the street and off the front page.

591
01:06:03,880 --> 01:06:06,060
They say it was just one guy or a creature.

592
01:06:06,640 --> 01:06:07,900
What's some asshole in the costume?

593
01:06:10,560 --> 01:06:14,240
This guy did deliver us one of the city's biggest crime lords.

594
01:06:14,640 --> 01:06:17,400
No one takes the law into their own hands in my city.

595
01:06:18,450 --> 01:06:18,730
Understand?

596
01:06:19,750 --> 01:06:20,670
No way to bury it now.

597
01:06:20,790 --> 01:06:22,210
Maybe so, but they're still Judge Faden.

598
01:06:22,430 --> 01:06:23,070
Got Faden covered.

599
01:06:23,430 --> 01:06:25,650
Okay, what about this bat they're babbling about?

600
01:06:25,750 --> 01:06:30,350
Even if these guys will swear in court to being thrashed by a giant bat, we've got Balconi at the scene.

601
01:06:31,370 --> 01:06:34,210
Drugs, prints, cargo manifests. This bat character gave us everything.

602
01:06:34,990 --> 01:06:36,370
Okay, let's do it.

603
01:06:39,930 --> 01:06:41,250
Bats are nocturnal.

604
01:06:41,410 --> 01:06:45,470
Bats may be, but even for billionaire playboys, three o'clock is pushing it.

605
01:06:46,650 --> 01:06:48,470
Price for leading a double life, I fear.

606
01:06:50,820 --> 01:06:52,180
Your theatrics made an impression.

607
01:06:54,860 --> 01:06:56,420
Metricality, deception.

608
01:06:57,780 --> 01:07:00,600
They're powerful weapons, Alfred. This is a good start.

609
01:07:01,400 --> 01:07:06,620
If those are to be the first of many injuries to come, it would be wise to find a suitable excuse.

610
01:07:07,420 --> 01:07:08,460
Polo, for instance.

611
01:07:08,660 --> 01:07:10,060
I'm not learning polo, Alfred.

612
01:07:10,780 --> 01:07:13,600
Strange injuries and non-existent social life.

613
01:07:14,660 --> 01:07:19,880
These things beg the question as to what exactly does Bruce Wayne do with his time and his money.

614
01:07:20,520 --> 01:07:21,680
What does someone like me do?

615
01:07:23,160 --> 01:07:24,200
Drive sports cars.

616
01:07:25,220 --> 01:07:26,120
Take movie stars.

617
01:07:28,080 --> 01:07:29,400
Buy things that are not for sale.

618
01:07:29,880 --> 01:07:31,000
Who knows, Master Wayne?

619
01:07:31,480 --> 01:07:35,630
You start pretending to have fun, you might even have a little by accident.

620
01:07:38,700 --> 01:07:41,210
Sir, we have a situation.

621
01:07:42,170 --> 01:07:42,510
All right.

622
01:07:43,070 --> 01:07:46,630
The Coast Guard picked up one of our cargo ships last night.

623
01:07:47,430 --> 01:07:49,330
Heavily damaged, all crew missing.

624
01:07:50,290 --> 01:07:50,930
Probably dead.

625
01:07:54,230 --> 01:07:56,590
The ship was carrying a prototype weapon.

626
01:07:56,710 --> 01:07:58,170
It's a microwave emitter.

627
01:07:58,790 --> 01:08:01,650
It's designed for desert warfare, but it...

628
01:08:03,470 --> 01:08:09,970
It looks like somebody, um, turned it on.

629
01:08:15,050 --> 01:08:19,510
It uses focused microwaves to vaporize the enemy's water supply.

630
01:08:27,430 --> 01:08:29,490
The damage to the ship was catastrophic.

631
01:08:30,470 --> 01:08:33,140
The weapon itself is, um...

632
01:08:34,910 --> 01:08:35,430
Missing?

633
01:08:37,340 --> 01:08:37,479
Yeah.

634
01:08:47,310 --> 01:08:48,210
I've seen another one.

635
01:08:58,439 --> 01:09:00,380
He's done something the police have never done.

636
01:09:00,600 --> 01:09:02,760
You can't take the law into your own hands.

637
01:09:03,080 --> 01:09:04,840
At least he's getting something dumb.

638
01:09:05,800 --> 01:09:06,920
Bruce, help me out here.

639
01:09:08,359 --> 01:09:12,319
Well, a guy who dresses up like a bat clearly has issues.

640
01:09:13,700 --> 01:09:15,740
But he's put Falcone behind bars.

641
01:09:16,100 --> 01:09:18,399
And now the cops want to bring him in, so what does that tell you?

642
01:09:18,640 --> 01:09:19,140
They're jealous.

643
01:09:20,060 --> 01:09:25,100
Sir, the pool is for decoration and your friends do not have swim room.

644
01:09:28,090 --> 01:09:29,529
Well, they're European.

645
01:09:31,910 --> 01:09:33,830
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

646
01:09:35,210 --> 01:09:36,930
It is not a question of money.

647
01:09:36,990 --> 01:09:45,890
You see, I'm buying this hotel and setting some new rules about the pool area.

648
01:09:48,410 --> 01:09:50,490
I think the Batman deserves a medal.

649
01:09:50,950 --> 01:09:52,790
And a straitjacket to pin it on.

650
01:10:02,850 --> 01:10:03,170
Bruce?

651
01:10:07,820 --> 01:10:08,160
Rachel?

652
01:10:09,820 --> 01:10:10,840
I heard you were back.

653
01:10:13,250 --> 01:10:13,850
What are you doing?

654
01:10:14,270 --> 01:10:16,050
Uh, just swimming.

655
01:10:17,010 --> 01:10:19,770
Wow, it is good to see you.

656
01:10:20,090 --> 01:10:21,030
You were gone a long time.

657
01:10:22,250 --> 01:10:23,850
I know. How are things?

658
01:10:24,470 --> 01:10:27,860
Same. Job's getting worse.

659
01:10:28,840 --> 01:10:30,860
Can't change the world on your own.

660
01:10:31,620 --> 01:10:32,680
What choice do I have?

661
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:35,750
When you're too busy swimming.

662
01:10:37,610 --> 01:10:40,950
Rachel, all of... all this...

663
01:10:43,050 --> 01:10:49,260
It's not me. It's... inside. I am...

664
01:11:00,470 --> 01:11:06,430
Bruce, deep down you may still be that same great kid you used to be.

665
01:11:09,050 --> 01:11:10,310
But it's not who you are underneath.

666
01:11:12,030 --> 01:11:13,590
It's what you do that defines you.

667
01:11:26,370 --> 01:11:28,010
Dr. Crane, thanks for coming.

668
01:11:28,210 --> 01:11:30,830
Not at all. He cut his wrists.

669
01:11:31,130 --> 01:11:32,910
Probably looking for the insanity plea.

670
01:11:33,470 --> 01:11:34,930
But if anything should happen...

671
01:11:35,070 --> 01:11:36,810
Of course. Better safe than sorry.

672
01:11:41,480 --> 01:11:44,700
Yeah, Dr. Crane, I can't take it anymore. It's all too much.

673
01:11:44,980 --> 01:11:47,180
The walls are closing in. Blah, blah, blah.

674
01:11:48,140 --> 01:11:49,520
Not a couple of days of this food.

675
01:11:50,060 --> 01:11:50,620
It'll be true.

676
01:11:51,660 --> 01:11:52,200
What do you want?

677
01:11:52,700 --> 01:11:55,840
I want to know how you're going to convince me to keep my mouth shut.

678
01:11:56,140 --> 01:11:56,640
About what?

679
01:11:57,040 --> 01:11:57,960
You don't know anything.

680
01:11:58,540 --> 01:12:01,900
I know you don't want the cops to take a closer look at the drugs they seized.

681
01:12:02,920 --> 01:12:06,080
I know about your experiments with the inmates of your nuthouse.

682
01:12:07,180 --> 01:12:10,220
See, I don't go into business with a guy without finding out his dirty secrets.

683
01:12:11,400 --> 01:12:13,520
You know, those goons you used.

684
01:12:14,500 --> 01:12:16,020
I own the muscle in this town.

685
01:12:16,440 --> 01:12:19,640
Now, I've been bringing your stuff in for months.

686
01:12:20,440 --> 01:12:22,860
So whatever he's planning, it's big.

687
01:12:23,520 --> 01:12:24,200
And I want it.

688
01:12:25,950 --> 01:12:27,910
Well, I already know what he'll say.

689
01:12:29,520 --> 01:12:30,540
That we should kill you.

690
01:12:32,530 --> 01:12:33,970
Even he can't get me in here.

691
01:12:34,770 --> 01:12:35,510
Not in my town.

692
01:12:41,950 --> 01:12:43,230
Would you like to see my mask?

693
01:12:44,950 --> 01:12:46,150
I use it in my experiments.

694
01:12:49,200 --> 01:12:53,050
He's probably not very frightening to a guy like you.

695
01:12:53,050 --> 01:12:54,940
With these crazies.

696
01:12:55,440 --> 01:12:56,320
He can't stand it.

697
01:12:57,650 --> 01:12:59,350
So when did the nut take over the nut house?

698
01:13:00,530 --> 01:13:02,550
They scream and they cry.

699
01:13:04,050 --> 01:13:05,210
Which is your game now?

700
01:13:08,910 --> 01:13:10,730
He's not faking. Not that one.

701
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:15,340
I'll talk to the judge and see if I can get him moved to the secure wing at Arkham.

702
01:13:15,600 --> 01:13:16,660
I can't treat him here.

703
01:13:45,770 --> 01:13:48,450
The scum is getting jumpy because you stood up to Falcone.

704
01:13:49,030 --> 01:13:51,890
It's a start. Your partner was at the docks for the Falcone.

705
01:13:52,730 --> 01:13:55,210
Oh, he Moonlights is a low level enforcer.

706
01:13:55,730 --> 01:13:58,750
They were splitting the shipment in two. Only half went to the dealers.

707
01:13:59,750 --> 01:14:01,390
Why? What about the other half?

708
01:14:02,010 --> 01:14:02,750
The Flask knows.

709
01:14:03,010 --> 01:14:03,790
He won't talk.

710
01:14:05,190 --> 01:14:06,070
He'll talk to me.

711
01:14:06,910 --> 01:14:09,750
Mission Love set up a massive task force to catch you.

712
01:14:10,330 --> 01:14:11,390
He thinks you're dangerous.

713
01:14:12,150 --> 01:14:12,790
What do you think?

714
01:14:14,720 --> 01:14:15,880
I think you're trying to help.

715
01:14:22,130 --> 01:14:23,230
But I've been wrong before.

716
01:14:35,290 --> 01:14:37,230
Man, I have kids to feed.

717
01:14:37,570 --> 01:14:38,690
Do I don't like falafel?

718
01:14:55,210 --> 01:14:56,650
Where were the other drugs going?

719
01:14:57,050 --> 01:15:01,350
I never knew. I don't know. I swear to God.

720
01:15:01,390 --> 01:15:02,350
Swear to me!

721
01:15:08,930 --> 01:15:11,270
I don't know. I never knew. Never.

722
01:15:11,750 --> 01:15:14,930
They went to some guy for a couple of days before they went to the dealer.

723
01:15:15,170 --> 01:15:15,390
Why?

724
01:15:17,240 --> 01:15:20,140
There was something. Something else in the drugs.

725
01:15:20,940 --> 01:15:22,220
Something hidden. What?

726
01:15:22,740 --> 01:15:24,040
I never went to the drop-off point.

727
01:15:24,840 --> 01:15:27,900
It was in the narrows. Cops only go there when they're in force.

728
01:15:28,080 --> 01:15:29,380
Do I look like a cop?

729
01:15:29,560 --> 01:15:30,060
Stop it!

730
01:15:30,960 --> 01:15:46,090
What am I talking about?

731
01:15:47,470 --> 01:15:48,260
What's your problem with it?

732
01:15:48,260 --> 01:15:49,010
It shouldn't exist.

733
01:15:49,630 --> 01:15:53,310
This ship left Singapore with 246 containers, but arrived with 247.

734
01:15:53,950 --> 01:15:55,810
So I'm guessing there's something I'm not supposed to find in there.

735
01:15:55,910 --> 01:15:59,030
Listen, counselor, we don't want to know what's in Mr. Falcone's crate.

736
01:15:59,990 --> 01:16:01,130
Things are working a little differently now.

737
01:16:01,770 --> 01:16:02,290
Open it up.

738
01:16:56,830 --> 01:16:57,910
It's you, isn't it?

739
01:16:58,230 --> 01:16:59,870
Everybody's been talking about you.

740
01:17:00,090 --> 01:17:01,130
Don't get in here!

741
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:04,320
The other kids won't believe me.

742
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:29,010
Bit of all traces.

743
01:17:30,550 --> 01:17:31,730
Gonna torch the whole place.

744
01:17:32,030 --> 01:17:32,370
All right.

745
01:20:01,390 --> 01:20:02,050
It's your birthday.

746
01:20:12,940 --> 01:20:14,150
This was so much more potent.

747
01:20:16,210 --> 01:20:16,830
Hallucinogen.

748
01:20:17,850 --> 01:20:19,530
Weaponized in aerosol form.

749
01:20:19,770 --> 01:20:22,390
You have been hanging out in the wrong clubs, Mr. Wayne.

750
01:20:22,870 --> 01:20:25,890
I called Mr. Fox when your condition worsened after the first day.

751
01:20:26,070 --> 01:20:30,630
I analyzed your blood, isolating the receptor compounds and the protein-based catalyst.

752
01:20:31,410 --> 01:20:33,050
I'm not going to understand any of that.

753
01:20:33,570 --> 01:20:34,030
Not at all.

754
01:20:34,850 --> 01:20:36,810
I just wanted you to know how hard it was.

755
01:20:37,310 --> 01:20:39,610
Bottom line, I synthesized an antidote.

756
01:20:39,810 --> 01:20:40,630
Could you make more?

757
01:20:40,970 --> 01:20:43,030
Are you planning on gassing yourself again, Mr. Wayne?

758
01:20:44,240 --> 01:20:45,550
You know how it is, Mr. Fox.

759
01:20:45,730 --> 01:20:47,150
You're out at night looking for kicks.

760
01:20:47,310 --> 01:20:49,850
Someone's passing around the weaponized to loosen the jets.

761
01:20:50,110 --> 01:20:51,090
I'll bring what I have.

762
01:20:51,310 --> 01:20:53,130
The antidote should inoculate you for now.

763
01:20:53,850 --> 01:20:55,230
Alfred, always a pleasure.

764
01:20:56,490 --> 01:21:03,600
Lucius, you sure you don't want to come in?

765
01:21:03,780 --> 01:21:04,840
I have to get back.

766
01:21:05,320 --> 01:21:06,560
I just wanted to leave this.

767
01:21:06,720 --> 01:21:06,980
Thank you.

768
01:21:06,980 --> 01:21:07,400
Rachel?

769
01:21:09,950 --> 01:21:12,390
Looks like someone's been burning the candle at both ends.

770
01:21:13,390 --> 01:21:14,510
Must have been quite an occasion.

771
01:21:15,030 --> 01:21:15,580
It is my birthday.

772
01:21:15,580 --> 01:21:16,450
I know.

773
01:21:17,210 --> 01:21:19,750
I'm sorry I can't come tonight. I was just dropping off your present.

774
01:21:19,830 --> 01:21:20,670
You've got better plans?

775
01:21:21,630 --> 01:21:23,470
My boss has been missing for two days,

776
01:21:23,890 --> 01:21:27,370
which in this town means that I should probably start by looking at the bottom of the river.

777
01:21:27,550 --> 01:21:27,830
Rachel.

778
01:21:31,970 --> 01:21:32,590
Rachel Doss.

779
01:21:33,950 --> 01:21:34,830
Who authorized that?

780
01:21:35,170 --> 01:21:37,550
Get Crane down there right now. Do not take no for an answer.

781
01:21:37,590 --> 01:21:40,990
Call Dr. Lehman. Tell him we'll need our own assessment on the judge's desk by morning.

782
01:21:41,810 --> 01:21:42,210
What's wrong?

783
01:21:42,790 --> 01:21:46,270
It's Falcone. Dr. Crane moved him to Arkham Asylum on suicide watch.

784
01:21:46,550 --> 01:21:49,070
You're going to Arkham now. It's in the Narrows, Rachel.

785
01:21:50,800 --> 01:21:51,760
You enjoy your party, Bruce.

786
01:21:52,740 --> 01:21:53,860
Some of us have work to do.

787
01:21:54,440 --> 01:21:55,080
You be careful.

788
01:22:18,260 --> 01:22:20,260
With Master Wayne, the guests will be arriving.

789
01:22:20,380 --> 01:22:21,680
Keep them happy until I arrive.

790
01:22:22,220 --> 01:22:23,400
Tell them that joke, you know.

791
01:23:08,010 --> 01:23:10,170
What's a big shot like you doing in a place like this?

792
01:23:10,910 --> 01:23:11,910
I need some information.

793
01:23:12,390 --> 01:23:16,910
The Wayne Antwerp 47B-1-M-E.

