01:51:45,050 --> 01:51:45,370
Oh, lady!

1054
01:51:45,850 --> 01:51:46,930
We're about to raise these bridges.

1055
01:51:46,930 --> 01:51:48,730
Officer, I'm a Gotham City District Attorney.

1056
01:51:48,790 --> 01:51:49,330
Let me pass.

1057
01:52:02,980 --> 01:52:04,020
Somebody here to see you.

1058
01:52:04,940 --> 01:52:05,640
What are you doing here?

1059
01:52:05,860 --> 01:52:08,880
A mutual friend sent me with this counter-x-creant toxin.

1060
01:52:09,380 --> 01:52:10,300
Hopefully you won't need it.

1061
01:52:11,040 --> 01:52:13,020
Unless he's got some way of getting that crap into the air.

1062
01:52:15,480 --> 01:52:16,500
All right, last one across.

1063
01:52:22,530 --> 01:52:24,350
I'd better get you off the island before they raise the bridges.

1064
01:52:24,430 --> 01:52:24,990
Patrolman!

1065
01:52:26,860 --> 01:52:27,120
Stop!

1066
01:52:54,640 --> 01:52:55,640
I can't find my mom.

1067
01:53:09,740 --> 01:53:13,150
Gentlemen, time to spread the word.

1068
01:53:15,900 --> 01:53:16,700
And the word turns.

1069
01:53:45,360 --> 01:53:45,720
Spiking.

1070
01:53:46,910 --> 01:53:47,550
Right there.

1071
01:53:48,730 --> 01:53:50,730
That water main is right under the Narrows.

1072
01:55:43,870 --> 01:55:45,390
The Narrows is tearing itself to pieces.

1073
01:55:45,630 --> 01:55:46,390
This is just the beginning.

1074
01:55:46,810 --> 01:55:48,190
If they hit the whole city with Toxin,

1075
01:55:48,250 --> 01:55:51,170
There's nothing to stop Gotham tearing itself apart from mass panic.

1076
01:55:51,370 --> 01:55:52,130
How are they gonna do that?

1077
01:55:52,290 --> 01:55:53,150
They'll be using the train.

1078
01:55:53,530 --> 01:55:57,130
The monorail follows the water mains to the central hub beneath Wayne Tower.

1079
01:55:57,610 --> 01:55:59,090
If they get their machine into Wayne Station,

1080
01:55:59,190 --> 01:56:02,570
it'll cause a chain reaction that'll vaporize the entire city's water supply.

1081
01:56:02,910 --> 01:56:04,650
Covering Gotham in this poison.

1082
01:56:04,730 --> 01:56:07,590
I'm gonna stop him from loading that train, but I may need your help.

1083
01:56:08,210 --> 01:56:08,670
What do you need?

1084
01:56:09,010 --> 01:56:09,750
Can you drive stick?

1085
01:56:17,970 --> 01:56:21,280
Nothing to fear, but fear itself.

1086
01:56:22,890 --> 01:56:24,210
I can hear the hell!

1087
01:56:25,390 --> 01:56:57,760
They will save us.

1088
01:56:58,000 --> 01:57:05,330
Luke, don't peek.

1089
01:57:14,440 --> 01:57:17,450
Mrs. Gordon, prepare to lower the bridge.

1090
01:57:33,470 --> 01:57:35,950
You could die. At least tell me your name.

1091
01:57:41,840 --> 01:57:48,120
It's not who I am underneath, but what I do that defines me.

1092
01:57:49,780 --> 01:57:50,120
Bruce?

1093
01:57:51,780 --> 01:58:27,870
You took my advice about theatricality a bit? Literally.

1094
01:58:28,230 --> 01:58:29,130
It ends here.

1095
01:58:29,450 --> 01:58:33,030
But you and the police, maybe. My fate, however, lies with the rest of Gotham.

1096
01:58:33,350 --> 01:58:35,600
Now, if you'll excuse me, I have a city to destroy.

1097
01:58:35,600 --> 01:58:38,130
I can't beat two of your pawns.

1098
01:58:38,950 --> 01:58:39,530
As you wish.

1099
01:58:53,470 --> 01:59:03,440
GPS online. It's in 100 yards.

1100
02:05:10,830 --> 02:05:18,300
I seem to remember firing you. You did. I got another job. Yours.

1101
02:05:20,000 --> 02:05:20,840
Who's authority?

1102
02:05:22,270 --> 02:05:26,510
Batman may have made the front page, but Bruce Wayne got pushed to page 8.

1103
02:05:34,420 --> 02:05:34,880
Bruce Wayne?

1104
02:05:35,260 --> 02:05:38,880
What makes you think you can decide who's running Wayne Enterprises?

1105
02:05:39,300 --> 02:05:40,480
Well, the fact that I'm the owner.

1106
02:05:40,720 --> 02:05:41,560
What are you talking about?

1107
02:05:42,260 --> 02:05:45,740
The company went public a week ago, and I bought most of the shares.

1108
02:05:46,220 --> 02:05:49,200
Through various charitable foundations and trusts and so forth.

1109
02:05:49,800 --> 02:05:55,100
Look, it's all a bit technical, but the important thing is that my company's future.

1110
02:05:57,070 --> 02:05:57,750
Right, Mr. Fox?

1111
02:05:58,350 --> 02:05:59,450
Right you are, Mr. Wayne.

1112
02:06:02,610 --> 02:06:03,530
Didn't you get the memo?

1113
02:06:04,130 --> 02:06:24,790
I didn't tell you, Rachel.

1114
02:06:25,230 --> 02:06:27,070
No, no, Bruce. I'm sorry.

1115
02:06:28,790 --> 02:06:30,710
The day that Chill died, I...

1116
02:06:33,360 --> 02:06:34,510
I said terrible things.

1117
02:06:35,370 --> 02:06:36,050
But true things.

1118
02:06:37,860 --> 02:06:39,300
I was a coward with a gun.

1119
02:06:39,900 --> 02:06:42,460
Justice is about more than revenge, so...

1120
02:06:42,820 --> 02:06:43,320
Thank you.

1121
02:06:44,630 --> 02:06:46,390
I never stopped thinking about you.

1122
02:06:48,890 --> 02:06:49,530
About us.

1123
02:06:50,070 --> 02:06:52,640
When I heard you were back, I...

1124
02:06:53,970 --> 02:06:54,970
I started to hope.

1125
02:07:20,320 --> 02:07:22,040
Then I found out about your mask.

1126
02:07:34,130 --> 02:07:36,860
Your real face is the one that criminals now fear.

1127
02:07:38,510 --> 02:07:39,390
A man I loved.

1128
02:07:41,030 --> 02:07:41,910
A man who vanished.

1129
02:07:43,830 --> 02:07:45,030
He never came back at all.

1130
02:08:12,970 --> 02:08:14,010
Prove me wrong, you know.

1131
02:08:14,530 --> 02:08:14,950
About what?

1132
02:08:18,710 --> 02:08:20,190
Father would be very proud of you.

1133
02:08:21,400 --> 02:08:22,080
Just like me.

1134
02:08:50,030 --> 02:08:50,750
What will you do?

1135
02:08:53,270 --> 02:08:53,850
Rebuild it.

1136
02:08:55,730 --> 02:08:57,310
Just the way it was, brick for brick.

1137
02:09:04,940 --> 02:09:05,960
Just the way it was, sir?

1138
02:09:08,420 --> 02:09:08,840
Yeah, why?

1139
02:09:09,680 --> 02:09:13,900
I thought this might be a good opportunity for improving the foundations.

1140
02:09:15,320 --> 02:09:16,380
In the southeast corner.

1141
02:09:17,500 --> 02:09:18,180
Precisely, sir.

1142
02:09:35,220 --> 02:09:36,780
I couldn't find any mob bosses.

1143
02:09:37,810 --> 02:09:38,490
Well, Sergeant.

1144
02:09:38,970 --> 02:09:40,270
Oh, it's Lieutenant now.

1145
02:09:40,690 --> 02:09:42,010
You really started something.

1146
02:09:42,530 --> 02:09:44,110
Bent cops running scared.

1147
02:09:44,570 --> 02:09:45,710
Hope on the streets.

1148
02:09:46,410 --> 02:09:46,590
But?

1149
02:09:47,390 --> 02:09:48,830
The Narrows is lost.

1150
02:09:50,510 --> 02:09:53,890
I still haven't picked up Crane or half the inmates of Arkham that he freed.

1151
02:09:55,050 --> 02:09:55,530
We will.

1152
02:09:56,890 --> 02:09:57,890
We can bring government.

1153
02:09:58,650 --> 02:09:59,690
What about escalation?

1154
02:10:00,110 --> 02:10:00,710
Escalation.

1155
02:10:01,290 --> 02:10:04,830
We start carrying semi-automatics, they buy automatics.

1156
02:10:05,830 --> 02:10:07,470
We start wearing Kevlar.

1157
02:10:08,290 --> 02:10:09,790
They buy armor-piercing rounds.

1158
02:10:10,470 --> 02:10:10,790
And...

1159
02:10:10,970 --> 02:10:12,870
And you're wearing a mask.

1160
02:10:14,320 --> 02:10:15,700
Jumping off rooftops.

1161
02:10:17,200 --> 02:10:18,040
Take this guy.

1162
02:10:19,660 --> 02:10:21,040
Arm robbery, double homicide.

1163
02:10:21,820 --> 02:10:24,860
Got a taste for the theatrical, like you.

1164
02:10:25,360 --> 02:10:26,360
Leaves a calling card.

1165
02:10:38,490 --> 02:10:39,590
I never said thank you.

